text: Parramatta is a suburb 23 kilometres west of Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. Parramatta sits on the bank of the Parramatta River and is in the middle of the Sydney metropolitan area. Parramatta has many facilities such as transport (a major railway station, numerous buses and light rail) and shops (a large shopping centre with major stores such as Woolworths and Coles and many individual stores). It is often a very busy city. ==Related pages== * Rose Hill, New South Wales ==References== Category:Suburbs of Sydney Category:1788 establishments in Australia
